text:
(1)
Feast of San Rocco (St. Roch), 1933, No. 4. The procession, in Cherry Street, looking east from about 128 Cherry Street. A floral candelabrum is carried by the foremost group.
August 16, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
No. 5. The same, a closer view of the group with the candelabrum.
August 16, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
No. 6. The same scene, a close-up of a group of little girls with a basket of flowers.
August 16, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Feast of San Rocco [Saint Roch].
